# {{ANALYSIS_RECORD_LABEL}} Bodies

## 0. Role Of This File

This file holds the detailed body of each {{ANALYSIS_RECORD_LABEL}}. The compact index is `docs/project/themes/theme-index.md`; the rules for opening a record are in `docs/project/themes/theme-rules.md`. Each body uses a numbered heading whose id matches the index row, then three subsections: Method, Results, and Interpretation. Keep the standard shape so records stay scannable. The body below is a marked example; replace it with real records.

### 1. Baseline Behavior On The Chosen Set (example)

Method: state what was done or decided, and against which base. Keep it short -- point to the `docs/method/algorithmic-levers.md` entry or the prompt that produced the result rather than restating detail. (Example: ran the unchanged pipeline on the chosen evaluation set to fix a reference point.)

Results: state the outcome plainly. Put numbers in `docs/evaluation/comparison.md` and reference the column here rather than duplicating tables. (Example: recorded the primary and secondary metrics as the E1 column; this is the reference the next {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}} compares against.)

Interpretation: what the result means, what was learned, and any follow-up or rejected direction. If an approach is ruled out, also record it in `docs/method/algorithmic-levers.md` section 3. (Example: the baseline is stable enough to compare against; the next lever to test is recorded in `docs/project/backlog/active-issues.md`.)

